==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[hund#Old English|hund]] < Germanic '''*hundaz''' < Proto-Indo-European '''*kwntós''', a variant of '''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Proto-Indo-European roots|*kwon-]]''' "dog".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/haʊnd/}}
*{{SAMPA|/haUnd/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{cattag|dogs}} A [[dog]], particularly a [[breed]] with a good sense of [[smell]] developed for [[hunt]]ing other animals.

